text:
Home » Sports » All Four 18-5A B/CS Teams Get a Win This Week All Four 18-5A B/CS Teams Get a Win This Week Posted by Zach Taylor Sports Sunday, October 18th, 2015 
All four 18-5A B/CS teams got a W this week… 
A&M Consolidated only scored once in the second half and still crushed Caney Creek 61–6. 
Vikings got two touchdown runs from Jarvis Lister as Bryan whipped Willis 38–24. 
Quarterback David Hobson threw for four touchdowns and ran for two as Rudder romped Livingston 64 – 19 matching the second-highest win total in program history. 
Cornerback Timarcus Davis intercepted three passes and recovered a fumble in College Station’ 42-21 win over Huntsville. 
Navasota slapped Sealy 31–7 
Buffalo lost to Lexington 43–14. 
And St. Joseph Catholic fell to Rosehill Christian 15–7.
